full_text:
Neat little CSS trick to get the scrollbar width (if present) without any JS:

`:root { --scrollbar-width: calc(100vw - 100%); }`

Now we can set an element to be the 'true' (no scrollbar) viewport width with something like `width: calc(100vw - var(--scrollbar-width));`
